      <npc_text>As you talk, a tired man in dusty, weathered clothes enters the inn and looks around. Several caravan crewmen carry his chests and bags inside. The man carefully inspects his belongings and after a brief conversation, pays the crewmen.

"Hail to you, master Gracius! It's been a while. How may we serve you?" The innkeeper's attention is on Gracius, which doesn't prevent him from gesturing to his servants to pour Gracius some wine - three fingers indicate the quality of the wine, roast a fresh bird over the coals, and move the chests to the storage.

"A room for me and storage for my goods. Find me a good loremaster and send one of your guards to make sure that I'm not disturbed," says Gracius, tossing the innkeeper a coin.</npc_text>
